metadata.name: UPLOAD.EXE #90
metadata.description:
No death in the metaverse 
100 billion mortal coils before us, reduced to silly memes 

Here then, a chance to right every wrong 
Or curse ourselves, forgetting we once counted days so keenly 

C:\SOULS>UPLOAD.EXE -commit -purge 
Irreversible operation. Are you sure? [Y/N] Y_ 

.....LFG 

---------------------------------------------------- 


Additional params 

&fullsize=true : 4096x4096 output 
&debug=true : Display generative figure outlines  
&notilt=true : Remove tilt-shift filter 


References 

How to draw a basic Human Figure Using Circles Only - Photoshop - Easy Anatomy Drawing Tutorial  
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TgIYpe4dPWo 


Libraries (refer licenses.js) 

pixijs/pixijs - Graphics 
bjornharrtell/jsts – Polygon routines 
meodai/poline - Colour routines 
jwagner/simplex-noise - Noise gen 
strainer/fdrandom - Random number gen

metadata.name: The Age of Automata #75
metadata.description:
This is an exploration of cellular automaton to find simplicity and beauty in mathematics.

First, a grid with random dimensions is created. A color palette is randomly selected from a large number of palettes, and a cellular automaton is formed based on one of the rules, and this operation may be repeated randomly to form a relatively more complex pattern. Finally, a number of geometries are combined with the automaton to make the mint harmonious and unique.

The idea was inspired by discoveries of Wolfram and Ciphrd’s artwork. 

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

I recently launched my Twitter, so if you have any questions and would like to know about my next work or have a suggestion, you can contact me through this account:

https://twitter.com/_XSaha

Made with P5js.

metadata.name: Dynamic Rhythms #15
metadata.description:
"Dynamic Rhythms" is a generative abstract art piece that explores the interplay between randomness and structure. The artwork is created using a combination of lines, circles, and bezier curves in varying stroke weights and colors. These shapes are positioned in a dynamic and unexpected way, creating a sense of movement and energy on the canvas. 

The use of randomness in the composition generates a unique and ever-changing visual experience, while the use of circles and lines creates a sense of underlying structure. The overall effect is a harmonious and captivating exploration of the balance between chaos and order. The use of black background make the shapes stand out more, giving the artwork a sense of depth and complexity.

Created with p5.js, 100% code

January 2023

metadata.name: The Passing of Time #118
metadata.description:
To celebrate the one-year anniversary of fx(hash), an animated piece that both signifies and illustrates the passing of time. The generative code is derived from Before/After, but adds a unique animation algorithm that causes the artwork to organically expand and contract. The art adapts to different screen sizes but will work best in full-screen mode on a wide-screen monitor.

The Passing of Time is written in plain JavaScript, with the compute-intensive t-SNE transformation implemented in AssemblyScript and compiled to WebAssembly (WASM) for maximum performance. No external libraries have been used.

<space bar>: Pause the animation.
0, 1, 2, 3, 4: Resolution, from lowest (0) to highest (4); default is 2. Try to lower the resolution if the animation isn't smooth.

50% of primary proceeds will be donated to Tezos Ukraine, https://donate.tezos.org.ua/.

Author:
Claus O. Wilke
https://clauswilke.com/art
https://twitter.com/clauswilke

metadata.name: sandspiral II #170
metadata.description: This is a re-imagining of my new forms 04: sand spirals mint from hic et nunc in April '21. (https://hen.hicathon.xyz/objkt/68268 ). It has been altered to produce unique mints. There are 12 different random traits seeded from the operation hash, but only four are visible: primary hue, secondary hue, initial rotation, and line width. All values are equal likelihood, so there is no "rarity" per se; aesthetic value is the only trait that matters.

metadata.name: Stripes Symphony #1
metadata.description:
"Stripes Symphony" is a vibrant piece of abstract art consisting of a series of stripes in various artistic colors. 

The stripes blend and flow into one another, creating a harmonious and melodic composition that captures the eye and sparks the imagination. The bold and dynamic lines of the stripes, combined with the energetic color palette, create a lively and uplifting atmosphere that draws the viewer in and invites them to explore the rich tapestry of hues and tones. 

This artwork is a celebration of color and movement, a vibrant and dynamic expression of the my creative spirit.

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #130
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: Dencity #704
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.
